"a.讽刺的，含沙射影的 【英】 adj. 讽刺的，含沙射影(sl yly disparaging；insinu ating) 【例】 a snide remark(刻毒的话) adj. (用意险恶的)讽刺的 【记】源于法国19世纪的讽刺学家施奈得. 【记】needle 针，象针一样尖刻地讽刺社会虚假与伪劣现象 snide (adj.)  1859, thieves' slang, ""counterfeit, sham, bad, spurious,"" of unknown origin. Of persons, ""cunning, sharp,"" from 1883. Sense of ""sneering"" is first attested 1933, perhaps via sense of ""hypocrisy, malicious gossip"" (1902). Related: Sneeringly."
